1
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:09,217
<i>There's a sign displayed
at the entrance of this town.</i>

2
00:00:09,926 --> 00:00:12,595
<i>A sign that was erected by the strong.</i>

3
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:19,102
<i>Bofurin is a group of Furin High students
who fight to protect the town.</i>

4
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:23,106
<i>Sakura, an outsider
who enrolled in Furin High,</i>

5
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:25,108
<i>on his first day during a lookout,</i>

6
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:28,153
<i>saved a middle school boy
who was chased by some guys.</i>

7
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:33,366
<i>However, the ones chasing the boy
were members of the Shishitoren,</i>

8
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:36,453
<i>a team that devotes itself to power.</i>

9
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:42,542
<i>Sakura's action escalates to an
all-out war between Shishitoren and Furin.</i>

10
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:49,007
<i>Shishitoren's leader, Choji Tomiyama,
then proposed a five-on-five match.</i>

11
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:54,137
<i>If Tomiyama were to defeat
the Furin's rep, Hajime Umemiya,</i>

12
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:58,683
<i>he along with the rest of Furin High
would fall into Shishitoren's hands.</i>

13
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:01,352
<i>And to take on that fight
they cannot afford to lose,</i>

14
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:05,482
<i>Sakura and the others
headed to Shishitoren's turf.</i>

15
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:49,961
Welcome to our turf!

16
00:02:50,044 --> 00:02:52,463
Thanks for having us.

17
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,353
Come on, over here!

18
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:10,315
{\an8}Hurry! Hurry!

19
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:23,953
Choji, you don't have to run.

20
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:36,216
Still, this place sure is full of pubs.

21
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:39,761
There are a lot of pubs
in Shishitoren's turf.

22
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:43,014
This place is apparently
the biggest bar district in the area.

23
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,892
I heard it gets really lively at night.

24
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:48,102
Not a safe place to be, though.

25
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,733
By the way, why are you here?

26
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:56,110
You're not gonna fight, right?

27
00:03:56,194 --> 00:04:00,281
Why, I was there when all of this started!
I'm involved in this!

28
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:03,493
Besides, I'm still part of Bofurin.

29
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:06,246
Even if I couldn't protect others
like the rest of you,

30
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:09,040
I want to at least be strong
enough to protect myself.

31
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:12,043
So let me learn a thing or two from this!

32
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,131
Suits yourself!

33
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:19,384
You get red so easily, Sakura-kun.

34
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:20,843
Shut up!

35
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,428
You shut up!

36
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:26,182
Sheesh, learn to take things seriously
for once.

37
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:29,310
And you should learn
to loosen up a bit, Hiragi.

38
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:31,187
-Sakura-san, let me message you...
-But...

39
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,773
-...before the fight!
-They seem reliable.

40
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:35,692
-I don't need it!
-Don't be shy!

41
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:43,199
Hey! Hurry! Hurry!

42
00:04:43,741 --> 00:04:45,243
This way!

43
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,633
Once again,

44
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:02,719
welcome...

45
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,352
to Shishitoren's headquarters.

46
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:15,690
{\an8}"Ori"?

47
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:16,774
{\an8}ORION STARS

48
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:30,580
Shishitoren's headquarters used to be
an abandoned theater named Orion Stars,

49
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,583
and now they just call it "Ori."

50
00:05:37,837 --> 00:05:40,590
Okay, let's go!

51
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:46,220
The fighters have entered the ring!

52
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,982
Start already!

53
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,777
-It's Umemiya.
-The guy next to him's Hiragi?

54
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,279
Come on! Show your faces!

55
00:06:03,362 --> 00:06:05,615
-Who's the guy behind 'em?
-Beats me.

56
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:10,328
Oh, I get it now.

57
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:13,873
"Ori" as in the word for cage.
A cage of beasts.

58
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:16,292
<i>Will we be able to get out of here?</i>

59
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:18,294
<i>Can we make it back alive?</i>

60
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:20,421
Didn't you come here to learn?

61
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:22,840
Keep your eyes forward.

62
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,348
Okay, guys!

63
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,354
Let's start our super-duper fun
one-on-one tournament!

64
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:42,110
Sheesh, they're really hyping this up
like it's some sort of festival.

65
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,195
All right, listen.

66
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:46,239
Things have gotten pretty big now,

67
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,491
but the main match is
between Tomiyama and me.

68
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:52,495
Nothing's riding on
your individual matches.

69
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,372
So just take it easy.

70
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,335
Screw that!

71
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:02,755
It doesn't matter if anything
is riding on them or not.

72
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,757
I have no plans of losing.

73
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,011
You heard him.

74
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,808
How reliable!

75
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:18,813
Now, Ume-chan! Let's do it! Hurry, hurry!

76
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:22,900
There, there. No tournament starts
with the generals' fight, okay?

77
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:24,110
Whaat?

78
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,532
Boss, can I go first?

79
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:35,371
That long mop over there's been staring
at me non-stop, it's gettin' on my nerves.

80
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:39,292
Wow, you got requested right
to the table, Sugishita-kun!

81
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,003
Sure, why not?

82
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:50,887
Hey!

83
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:56,684
I haven't settled things with you yet.

84
00:07:56,767 --> 00:08:01,147
But I don't ever wanna fight a guy
who'd lose to these lame-asses.

85
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,066
Hey, are you listening to me?

86
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,943
I'm telling you not to lose, okay?

87
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:13,242
-Get him!
-Arima!

88
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,119
-Kill him!
-Beat his ass!

89
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:17,330
Arima... Arima...

90
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:18,956
Oh, there he is!

91
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:23,044
Yukinari Arima. He seemed
to be quite a power type.

92
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:26,255
{\an8}He once broke several bones
in a guy's ribs in one punch?

93
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,673
{\an8}There, there.

94
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,843
{\an8}Sugishita-kun's more or less the same,
so it should be fine.

95
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,011
{\an8}Nah.

96
00:08:32,553 --> 00:08:35,014
I'd feel bad for him
if you lumped them together.

97
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:36,265
Huh?

98
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:43,981
Sheesh.

99
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:47,193
Your eyes really piss me off.

100
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:57,745
Whoa, Umemiya! What happened to you?

101
00:09:05,586 --> 00:09:09,090
Don't look away durin' a fight, you moron!

102
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,225
You forgot the "-san..."

103
00:09:30,861 --> 00:09:32,196
Weak.

104
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,163
It's Umemiya-san,

105
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,498
you moron.

106
00:10:01,475 --> 00:10:03,269
Whoa, you got to be kidding me.

107
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,396
Huh? Seriously?

108
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:06,772
He beat Arima.

109
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,025
Do you know that guy?

110
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:11,652
Never seen him before.
Maybe he's a first-year?

111
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:13,404
In...

112
00:10:13,487 --> 00:10:15,364
In just one punch?

113
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:19,118
This can't be happening. Arima.

114
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:28,002
Wow! You're really tough!

115
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:37,637
What's your name?

116
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:39,680
Fight me next!

117
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,557
Stop it, Choji.

118
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:44,435
Sit still and wait for your turn.

119
00:10:45,102 --> 00:10:47,647
Not only are they not worried
their guy lost,

120
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,608
they're even complementing the enemy.

121
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:54,028
<i>I thought this too back then, but...</i>

122
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:57,990
those people are really insane.

123
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,993
Welcome back!

124
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:03,788
Man, you're as aggressive as usual!

125
00:11:03,871 --> 00:11:05,748
How's your face? You all right?

126
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,294
You've always been so tough!

127
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:14,298
Sugishita-san is amazing!

128
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:16,884
He's perfectly fine
even after getting hit like that!

129
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:18,636
Well, that's him all right.

130
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:21,847
Are you not surprised at all, Sakura-san?

131
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:24,600
Well, I did fight him once already.

132
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,980
So you acknowledge his strength,
too, Sakura-kun?

133
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:31,440
No, I'm not!

134
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,401
I only said I know he's tough!

135
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,529
-What's that face for?
-Yeah, we believe you.

136
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:37,947
Then why are you smiling?

137
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:40,991
Kame-chan, how would you
beat that long hair guy?

138
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:43,786
Kame-chan?

139
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:54,713
Okay, let's move on to the next match!

140
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,883
Hey, you two over there.

141
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:01,804
Clear that up for us.

142
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:06,809
Hurry it up!

143
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:07,810
Yes, sir.

144
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,481
Man, he's heavy.

145
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:15,359
There's no way we can carry him
all the way off the stage.

146
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:17,611
Let's just dump him off here.

147
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:23,993
Sheesh, he's always actin' like
he's the boss, but look at him now.

148
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:25,327
Dumbass.

149
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,079
Serves you right.

150
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:29,206
How mean...

151
00:12:32,543 --> 00:12:35,671
Hey, your little chatty chatter
is annoyin' the hell outta me.

152
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:43,262
Don't you all dare to go braggin' about
being the devotees of power again.

153
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:48,392
Just watchin' you is making me
feel embarrassed, you scrubs.

154
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:50,394
Huh?

155
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:54,398
Sakura-kun, nothing you say
is going to get through.

156
00:12:55,566 --> 00:13:00,279
These kind of kids won't understand
unless they get beaten themselves.

157
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:03,908
Huh? Then why don't you try it?

158
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:04,867
Whoa...

159
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:05,868
Hey.

160
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:08,954
You're not the one who's
going to face that kid.

161
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:11,874
Back off.

162
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:20,007
Okay, let's go next!
Next, next! Who's up next?

163
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,800
Then I'll...

164
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:23,093
Don't be silly.

165
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,678
Based on the order, I'm next.

166
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,514
Who're you callin' silly?

167
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,016
Hey, little boy.

168
00:13:30,851 --> 00:13:32,728
You seem really stressed.

169
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:34,522
Why don't we exercise a bit?

170
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,817
Numa-chan! Get him!

171
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:39,860
Yeah!

172
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,820
-Fight! Fight!
-Take him down!

173
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:44,365
Sakura-kun.

174
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,574
What?

175
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:49,411
When you said you came
to usurp the leadership...

176
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:51,372
I thought you were stupid.

177
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:54,458
Are you tryin' to pick a fight with me?
Sure, I'll take you on!

178
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:55,584
Calm down.

179
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,587
Sorry.

180
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:01,340
I thought you were just
howling empty threats.

181
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:05,469
But I found there is a solid core
in both your words and actions.

182
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:08,847
And that makes me think
you're pretty cool.

183
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:13,852
So, in order not to lose to you,
I'm going to give it my all, too.

184
00:14:18,857 --> 00:14:20,192
Just get up there already!

185
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:22,152
Kanuma!

186
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,696
Get him good!

187
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:27,032
Send him flying!

188
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,577
Tell me, what's his deal?

189
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:32,913
Oh, Kanuma-san, right? Wait just a second...

190
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:34,748
Nah, I'm not talking about him.

191
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,709
Huh? You mean Suo-san?

192
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:40,796
He's been famously strong
ever since his middle school days.

193
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,465
I could tell that just by looking.
Anything else?

194
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,092
What? Just by looking?

195
00:14:45,175 --> 00:14:46,468
Who cares about that now?

196
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:48,679
Well, about that...

197
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:51,181
He's famous,

198
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:55,519
but there aren't a lot of details
about him, like who he won against.

199
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:57,605
Huh? What's up with that?

200
00:14:57,688 --> 00:15:02,943
Yeah, I've heard his name quite a lot,
but I don't know any details about him.

201
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,279
He went to a different middle school, too.

202
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:08,198
I don't know much about Suo either, but...

203
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,200
it is clear to me now I met him...

204
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:15,664
He's a gentleman.

205
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:20,210
It's you guys' fault that Arima's...

206
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:23,464
Oh? You know
how to be mad for your friend?

207
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,300
<i>That's quite different from back then.</i>

208
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:30,679
Armia and I were always together...

209
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:35,309
Anyone would be pissed
if their bro got beat into the ground!

210
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:40,564
You only wail when you're the victim?

211
00:15:41,398 --> 00:15:43,817
You're just like a whiny child.

212
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:47,571
<i>He's gentle... huh?</i>

213
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:51,033
You must've had it so hard, little boy.

214
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:55,204
<i>Would a gentle person make such a face?</i>

215
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:08,092
Tantrums are only cute when kids do them.

216
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:13,973
Now, why don't you join me and take
a step up the stairway to adulthood?

217
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,855
What happened just now?

218
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:25,985
<i>He got behind me in a flash!</i>

219
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:29,113
<i>That movement...
He must've practiced some martial arts.</i>

220
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:32,616
<i>In that case, I just have to hit him
fast enough so he can't dodge!</i>

221
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,581
That was quite a fall.

222
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:44,461
You asshole!

223
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,802
I've got a question for you.

224
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:57,182
What do you think is needed
for someone to become an adult?

225
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:02,479
Why don't you join me and take
a step up the stairway to adulthood?

226
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:08,610
Stop spouting nonsense!

227
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,906
Wow...

228
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,325
It's like he fell on his own.

229
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:19,455
You moron!

230
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:22,458
-Take this seriously!
-Why're you letting him toy with you?

231
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,460
Stop fooling around, Kanuma!

232
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,754
Are you messing with us?

233
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:30,883
<i>They don't know anything...</i>

234
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:35,554
<i>Me? Fooling around? Every time
I try to push, pull, or grab him,</i>

235
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:37,890
<i>he turns it around on me
in a blink of an eye!</i>

236
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:42,394
<i>If you guys have stuff to say,
then go ahead and fight this guy!</i>

237
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,523
He's not just gentle, huh?

238
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:48,776
There isn't a shred of gentleness in him.

239
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:51,153
He's sure got quite a rotten personality.

240
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,196
Huh?

241
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:56,033
He's keepin' a guy weaker than him
in play, making a fool of him,

242
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:59,620
and showing off an overwhelming difference
in strength endlessly.

243
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:07,419
If it were me up there,
I'd much rather die.

244
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,213
I see...

245
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:11,298
I won't end up like that, though.

246
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:13,383
Yeah, it does sound morbid.

247
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:19,098
Well, I'm sure he has his own thoughts
about watching the Shishitoren punks.

248
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:22,893
But I'm surprised to see him
get this emotional.

249
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,354
This is probably
one of those cases, right?

250
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:29,775
When someone close by
is drawing out that side of him.

251
00:18:29,858 --> 00:18:31,276
<i>Now he mentions that...</i>

252
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,278
I'm going to give my all, too.

253
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:35,197
Say.

254
00:18:35,739 --> 00:18:36,824
Yes?

255
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:41,245
What do you think I could do
to make him fight me seriously?

256
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:42,788
Huh? Why would you?

257
00:18:48,585 --> 00:18:50,003
You punk!

258
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,176
You punk!

259
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:16,321
Come on, get the hell up!

260
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:18,991
Stop screwin' around, Kanuma!

261
00:19:19,074 --> 00:19:21,410
Are you even being serious right now?

262
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:34,506
<i>Huh? No way...</i>

263
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:37,759
<i>At this rate...</i>

264
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:45,392
Have you finally figured out the answer?

265
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,812
How about I...

266
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:51,190
No, no, no...

267
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:53,817
No...

268
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:57,196
This isn't happening! Not happening!

269
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,616
This is...

270
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:03,327
not happening!

271
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:12,544
How about I take a guess...

272
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:15,339
on what you're thinking right now?

273
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:20,677
<i>You're imagining yourself being
that very thing you once laughed at.</i>

274
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:24,473
That's the answer to my question.

275
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:27,184
What you need to become an adult?

276
00:20:28,143 --> 00:20:29,937
It's the power of imagination.

277
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:39,321
Come on.

278
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,199
Now you've got that done,
you're on the right track!

279
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:44,826
Let's move on to the next step
before you forget!

280
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:50,666
What do you think is necessary
to strengthen that imagination?

281
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:53,252
The answer is...

282
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:56,421
to make your imagination into reality.

283
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,720
-Wai...
-All right, stop.

284
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:06,640
That's enough.

285
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:10,394
Sorry, eye-patch-kun. Can you step down?

286
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:13,105
Huh? It's over?

287
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:17,109
Why?

288
00:21:17,192 --> 00:21:20,362
Don't embarrass us any further.

289
00:21:21,363 --> 00:21:24,366
Though, I guess it's not
an embarrassment anymore.

290
00:21:25,742 --> 00:21:27,661
Since you're not one of us anymore.

291
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:43,510
To become an adult means to
engage in other people's feelings.

292
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:47,514
For that, you'll need both
imagination and experience.

293
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:49,391
Good for you.

294
00:21:50,517 --> 00:21:54,354
You've managed to at least
take one step up those stairs.

295
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:35,455
Shishitoren's headquarters sure
has a strong atmosphere.

296
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:39,084
Is this a run-down theater?

297
00:23:40,043 --> 00:23:44,047
{\an8}Oh, I've heard about the
shark movie with this poster.

298
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:47,467
{\an8}Huh? This one is also a shark movie?

299
00:23:48,385 --> 00:23:50,303
{\an8}This one, too?

300
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:53,306
{\an8}Hey, look. This one too.

301
00:23:53,390 --> 00:23:54,766
{\an8}All sharks...

302
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,854
{\an8}No wonder it went under.

